ntal%20Scars%20After%20Turbulence-Hit%20Flight%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20extreme%20turbulence%20on%20Singapore%20Airlines%20(SIA)%20flight%20SQ321%20-%20which%20left%20one%20passenger%20dead%20from%20a%20suspected%20heart%20attack%20and%20dozens%20injured%20-%20has%20inflicted%20psychological%20scars%20on%20those%20who%20survived%2C%20it%20emerged%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20passenger%2C%20describing%20the%20ordeal%20as%20%26quot%3Bquite%20scary%26quot%3B%2C%20declared%20that%20he%20may%20not%20fly%20again%20for%20a%20while.%20Another%20said%20he%20threw%20up%20after%20waking%20up%20on%20the%20plane%20floor%2C%20following%20the%20turbulence%2C%20to%20the%20sound%20of%20people%20crying%20and%20the%20sight%20of%20blood%2C%20The%20Straits%20Times%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%2C%20which%20left%20London's%20Heathrow%20Airport%20for%20Singapore%20on%20May%2021%2C%20experienced%20extreme%20turbulence%20for%2062%20seconds%20over%20the%20Irrawaddy%20Basin%20around%2010%20hours%20after%20departure.%20It%20was%20then%20diverted%20to%20Thailand's%20Suvarnabhumi%20Airport%20for%20an%20emergency%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pilot%20diverted%20the%20plane%20carrying%20211%20passengers%20and%2018%20crew%20members%20to%20Bangkok's%20Suvarnabhumi%20Airport%20after%20declaring%20a%20medical%20emergency%2C%20before%20making%20an%20emergency%20landing%20at%203%3A45%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMental%20health%20professional%20Amanda%20Oh%2C%20founder%20of%20Budding%20Space%2C%20said%20a%20traumatic%20experience%20can%20make%20it%20difficult%20for%20a%20person%20to%20understand%20or%20process%20a%20situation%2C%20much%20like%20%26quot%3Ban%20indigestion%20in%20the%20mind%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20such%20a%20unique%20experience%20as%20what%20the%20passengers%20had%20to%20go%20through%2C%20it%20would%20be%20an%20extremely%20overwhelming%20experience%20for%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20broadsheet%20quoted%20Dr%20Oh%20as%20saying.%20This%20could%20cause%20psychological%20pain%20and%20physiological%20distress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20were%20on%20board%20the%20flight%20could%20experience%20mental%20health%20issues%2C%20including%20acute%20stress%20disorder%20(ASD)%2C%20post-traumatic%20stress%20disorder%20(PTSD)%20and%20anxiety%20disorders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20passengers%20on%20SQ321%20included%2041%20Singaporeans%2C%20with%20the%20remaining%20170%20from%20countries%20such%20as%20Australia%2C%20India%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20New%20Zealand%20and%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dead%20passenger%20has%20been%20identified%20as%20a%2073-year-old%20Briton%2C%20Geoff%20Kitchen.%20He%20was%20a%20retired%20insurance%20professional%20and%20musical%20theatre%20director%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20death%2C%20according%20to%20British%20media%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%2041%20passengers%20remain%20hospitalised%20across%20three%20hospitals%20in%20Bangkok%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20update%20from%20Samitivej%20Srinakarin%20Hospital%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Annabelle%20Chow%20-%20the%20principal%20clinical%20psychologist%20at%20Annabelle%20Psychology%20-%20said%20that%20up%20to%20a%20month%20after%20the%20incident%2C%20those%20affected%20may%20experience%20ASD%2C%20which%20includes%20symptoms%20such%20as%20recurrent%20and%20involuntary%20flashbacks%2C%20appetite%20and%20sleep%20changes%2C%20as%20well%20as%20memory%20gaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20they%20may%20be%20diagnosed%20with%20PTSD%20instead%20if%20symptoms%20persist%20past%20the%20one-month%20mark.%20PTSD%20has%20been%20known%20to%20affect%20a%20person's%20social%20functioning%20and%20physical%20well-being%2C%20said%20Dr%20Chow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20also%20develop%20an%20anxiety%20disorder%2C%20and%20experience%20panic%20attacks%20and%20physiological%20responses%20like%20a%20rapid%20heartbeat%2C%20sweating%20and%20nausea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Oh%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20incident%20could%20also%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bvicariously%20traumatic%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20loved%20ones%20of%20those%20on%20board%20SQ321%2C%20who%20could%20develop%20similar%20reactions%20despite%20not%20having%20been%20on%20the%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20gave%20reassurance%2C%20however%2C%20that%20with%20adequate%20support%2C%20%26quot%3Btrauma's%20impact%20on%20the%20brain%20is%20reversible%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20increase%20their%20feelings%20of%20perceived%20safety%2C%20passengers%20should%20maintain%20a%20healthy%20lifestyle%20and%20take%20part%20in%20activities%20involving%20bilateral%20stimulation%20like%20walking%20and%20swimming%2C%20which%20would%20help%20the%20mind%20process%20the%20traumatic%20experience%20better%2C%20said%20Dr%20Oh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFamily%20members%20can%20also%20play%20their%20part%20by%20being%20accommodating%20during%20this%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20if%20(the%20traumatised%20individuals)%20want%20to%20cry%20or%20talk%20about%20it%2C%20let%20them%20do%20that.%20Let%20them%20choose%20their%20way%20to%20grieve%20and%20process%20the%20experience%20in%20a%20way%20that%20they%20are%20comfortable%20with%20rather%20than%20hurrying%20them%20along%20that%20journey%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Oh%2C%20stressing%20that%20a%20sense%20of%20autonomy%20and%20control%20would%20improve%20their%20sense%20of%20perceived%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Thomas%20Lee%2C%20medical%20director%20at%20Resilienz%20clinic%2C%20recommended%20eye%20movement%20desensitisation%20and%20reprocessing%20(EMDR)%20-%20a%20popular%20method%20in%20trauma%20therapy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20treatment%2C%20done%20by%20a%20trained%20specialist%2C%20could%20help%20reduce%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20traumatic%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20the%20passengers%2C%20the%20cabin%20crew%20may%20experience%20a%20worse%20impact%20on%20their%20mental%20health%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Singapore%20daily%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20may%20think%20that%20they%20are%20used%20to%20turbulence%20but%20this%20is%20a%20bad%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Lee%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20would%20be%20good%20if%20early%20intervention%20counselling%20is%20provided%20to%20the%20cabin%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20three%20experts%2C%20while%20hopeful%20that%20recovery%20is%20possible%2C%20agreed%20that%20the%20duration%20will%20depend%20on%20the%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20his%20experience%2C%20said%20Dr%20Lee%2C%20recovery%20could%20take%20months%20or%20even%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20of%20distress%20felt%20by%20an%20individual%20during%20the%20flight%20-%20determined%20by%20factors%20such%20as%20whether%20they%20were%20hit%20by%20an%20object%20during%20the%20turbulence%20-%20would%20also%20influence%20the%20recovery%20time%2C%20said%20Dr%20Chow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecovery%20could%20also%20be%20drawn%20out%20if%20the%20patient%20has%20other%20unresolved%20traumas%2C%20Dr%20Oh%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20individual%20has%20previous%20unresolved%20traumas%20such%20as%20abuse%2C%20the%20SQ321%20experience%20would%20trigger%20those%20other%20unresolved%20traumas%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20would%20likely%20require%20a%20longer%20recovery%20time%20simply%20because%20they%20would%20be%20uncovering%20all%20these%20other%20unresolved%20traumas%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Oh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20stressed%2C%20however%2C%20that%20increasing%20the%20sense%20of%20perceived%20safety%20would%20ultimately%20be%20helpful%20for%20those%20who%20are%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20traumatised%20by%20the%20turbulence%20on%20SQ321.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20turbulence-hit%20SIA%20plane%20returned%20to%20Singapore%20on%20Sunday%20after%20being%20cleared%20for%20departure%20from%20Bangkok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%2