insider.com%2F6650a213a961b37edf39a568%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENoland%20Arbaugh%20received%20the%20implant%20in%20January%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENoland%20Arbaugh%20is%20the%20first%20human%20to%20receive%20Neuralink's%20brain-chip%20implant.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%2029-year-old%C2%A0quadriplegic%20man%20said%20it's%C2%A0helped%20him%20regain%20independence%20and%20reconnect%20socially.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20about%20how%20it's%20impacted%20his%20life%20since%20he%20got%20it%20inserted%20in%20January.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Noland%20Arbaugh%2C%20Neuralink's%20first%20human%20patient%20to%20receive%20its%20brain-chip%20implant.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20wasn't%20scared%20going%20into%20the%20surgery%20to%20get%20Neuralink's%20implant%20inserted%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20at%20peace%20with%20it%20all%3B%20it%20had%20much%20to%20do%20with%20my%20faith%20in%20God.%20I%20knew%20that%20whatever%20was%20to%20come%20was%20God's%20plan%20for%20my%20life%2C%20and%20that%20really%20put%20me%20at%20ease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20had%20complete%20faith%20in%20the%20teams%20working%20on%20this%2C%20including%20the%20surgical%20staff%20and%20nurses.%20They%20were%20all%20excellent%20people%20in%20their%20fields%2C%20and%20all%20my%20questions%20were%20very%20well%20answered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20risks%20involved%2C%20especially%20being%20the%20first%20to%20have%20it.%20The%20one%20thing%20I%20was%20worried%20about%20was%20getting%20brain%20damage.%20That%20was%20the%20one%20thing%20that%20gave%20me%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20pause%20beforehand.%20I%20told%20my%20parents%20that%20if%20I%20became%20mentally%20handicapped%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20want%20them%20to%20take%20care%20of%20me%20anymore%20and%20to%20put%20me%20in%20an%20assisted%20care%20home.%20That%20was%20probably%20the%20hardest%20thing%20I%20had%20to%20prepare%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2256300d0a-f885-4f6f-b52b-04e60a59de42%5C%22%3EThe%20idea%20of%20giving%20up%20the%20implant%20was%20really%20hard%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20month%20after%20I%20got%20it%2C%20some%20of%20the%20device's%20wires%2C%20or%20threads%2C%20retracted%20from%20my%20brain.%20This%20was%20not%20Neuralink's%20fault.%20There%20is%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20literature%20or%20studies%20about%20the%20subject%20and%20how%20much%20the%20brain%20moves%20when%20it%20pulses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20talked%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20brain%20surgeons%20and%20came%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20brain%20moves%20about%20a%20millimeter.%20Then%2C%20after%20they%20implanted%20it%20in%20my%20brain%2C%20they%20found%20that%20it%20moved%20three%20millimeters%2C%20which%20is%20three%20times%20as%20much%20as%20what%20they%20had%20expected.%20The%20components%20and%20threads%20that%20they%20built%20weren't%20intended%20to%20take%20on%20that%20kind%20of%20load%2C%20which%20caused%20them%20to%20retract%20a%20bit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20found%20out%20what%20happened%2C%20my%20initial%20response%20was%20to%20ask%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20go%20in%2C%20remove%20it%2C%20and%20insert%20a%20new%20one%2C%20but%20they%20told%20me%20they%20weren't%20considering%20it%20at%20the%20time.%20They%20wanted%20to%20see%20if%20they%20could%20work%20around%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20software%2C%20which%20they%20ended%20up%20doing%20instead%20of%20fixing%20it%20through%20another%20surgery.%20They%20handled%20it%20really%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20physically%20hurt%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20dangerous.%20But%20it%20hurt%20emotionally%20because%20I%20thought%20that%20I%20wasn't%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20use%20the%20device%20anymore.%20I%20was%20just%20down%20in%20the%20dumps%20for%20a%20few%20days%2C%20but%20I%20tend%20to%20roll%20with%20the%20punches.%20It%20took%20me%20a%20few%20days%2C%20but%20I%20came%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222026946e-679f-41a2-af4f-8381866a28f6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20use%20the%20implant%20to%20interact%20with%20people%20on%20social%20media%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20using%20it%20to%20message%20people%20on%20X%2C%20use%20Instagram%2C%20reply%20to%20emails%2C%20play%20fantasy%20sports%2C%20read%20comics%20online%2C%20and%20access%20a%20site%20I%20use%20to%20learn%20Japanese.%20I%20also%20used%20it%20to%20book%20a%20hotel%20for%20when%20I%20visited%20Neuralink's%20headquarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20time%20I%20fell%20asleep%20while%20using%20it%2C%20and%20the%20cursor%20still%20moves%20when%20I'm%20asleep%20and%20still%20clicks%20stuff.%20I%20fell%20asleep%20for%20about%20five%20minutes%20and%20when%20I%20woke%20up%2C%20there%20were%20around%2010%20different%20applications%20open%20on%20the%20computer.%20You%20can%20turn%20the%20cursor%20off%20so%20that%20doesn't%20happen%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20on%20this%20occasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20device%20connects%20to%20my%20computer%20using%20Bluetooth%2C%20and%20there's%20a%20Neuralink%20app%20that%20allows%20the%20implant%20to%20access%20the%20computer%2C%20so%20I%20can%20connect%20and%20disconnect%20from%20it%20at%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20I%20start%20my%20day%20at%207%20a.m.%20and%20use%20the%20implant%20until%2011%20p.m.%20I%20know%20it's%20a%20long%20day%2C%20but%20it's%20fun%20for%20me%2C%20so%20it%20doesn't%20really%20feel%20like%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20study%20sessions%20with%20a%20brain-computer%20interface%20team%20in%20Maryland%20for%20four%20to%20eight%20hours%20a%20day.%20Outside%20those%2C%20I%20have%20structured%20sessions%20where%20I%20have%20personal%20time%20to%20use%20the%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20helps%20us%20learn%20things%20that%20the%20researchers%20otherwise%20wouldn't%2C%20like%20different%20ways%20in%20which%20it%20doesn't%20quite%20work%20as%20intended.%20It%20can%20be%20a%20bug%20in%20the%20software%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20they%20need%20to%20address%2C%20which%20helps%20to%20make%20it%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202a4d68f-7059-475e-b48a-09bb22870529%5C%22%3EIt's%20served%20to%20make%20my%20life%20just%20a%20bit%20better%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20allowed%20me%20to%20reconnect%20with%20the%20world%2C%20my%20friends%2C%20and%20my%20family.%20It's%20made%20me%20a%20better%20texter%20and%20more%20capable%20of%20interacting%20with%20people%20such%20as%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20big%20things%20about%20being%20a%20quadriplegic%20is%20just%20how%20powerless%20you%20are%2C%20and%20so%20I%20wanted%20to%20take%20back%20as%20much%20control%20as%20I%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20times%20in%20the%20days%20after%20my%20accident%20in%202016%20that%20led%20to%20a%20spinal%20cord%20injury%20when%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20do%20anything%2C%20where%20I%20was%20sad%2C%20and%20I%20was%20like%2C%20'This%20sucks.'%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20I%20was%20doing%20for%20a%20few%20months%20and%20didn't%20feel%20like%20I%20was%20being%20very%20productive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I've%20always%20been%20the%20kind%20of%20person%20who%20accepts%20what%20is%2C%20and%20finds%20a%20way%20to%20move%20forward%2C%20and%20that's%20exactly%20what%20I%20did.%20I%20didn't%20wallow%20so%20much%20as%20I%20looked%20forward%20and%20thought%2C%20'How%20can%20I%20make%20my%20life%20better%3F%20How%20can%20I%20improve%20my%20life%20even%20a%20little%20bit%20today%3F'%20That%20helps%20a%20lot.%20It%20gives%20me%20a%20drive%20and%20a%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two-year%20mark%20after%20my%20accident%20was%20pretty%20hard.%20They%20say%20after%20two%20years%2C%20you%20won't%20recover%20any%20more%20movement%20or%20sensation%2C%20and%20that's%20basically%20what%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20left%20with%20for%20the%20rest%20of