rs%20of%20my%20life.%20When%20I%20was%20little%2C%20I%20stood%20on%20his%20feet%20to%20dance.%20We%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwife-and-i-sit-in-silence-dine-out-still-happy-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewent%20on%20dinner%20dates%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We%20traveled%20a%20lot.%20We%20grew%20up%20backstage%20at%20the%20Bob%20Marley%20Festival%20because%20of%20the%20relationships%20he%20fostered%20with%20the%20family.%20He%20was%20in%20the%20garment%20industry%2C%20probably%20the%20origin%20of%20my%20love%20of%20statement%20tees.%20I%20grew%20up%20feeling%20insanely%20lucky.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cee6469-54f2-4e21-9bce-2c773e8baebb%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20parents%20divorced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Five-been-through-divorce-on-both-ends-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20parents%20divorced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20when%20I%20was%2021.%20That%20was%20the%20first%20shift%20in%20our%20relationship.%20He%20went%20into%20a%20downward%20spiral%2C%20which%20led%20to%20our%20estrangement.%20It%20was%20hard%20not%20to%20take%20sides%20as%20I%20watched%20my%20mom's%20car%20get%20repossessed%20because%20he%20stopped%20paying.%20I%20tried%20to%20maintain%20a%20separate%20relationship%20and%20compartmentalize%20the%20complications%20of%20being%20a%20child%20of%20an%20acrimonious%20divorce.%20I%20bounced%20between%20anger%20and%20nostalgia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20knew%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-remarried-after-divorce-raising-sons-blended-family-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20divorced%20and%20remarried%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20but%20never%20met%20my%20daughters.%20I'd%20rather%20them%20not%20know%20him%2C%20then%20love%20him%20and%20risk%20the%20torment%20that%20came%20with%20the%20territory.%20He%20lived%20in%20a%20dilapidated%20assisted%20living%2C%20was%20missing%20teeth%2C%20and%20couldn't%20stand.%20I%20kept%20him%20at%20bay%20to%20avoid%20the%20inevitable%20heartache%20that%20came%20with%20being%20his%20daughter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20health%20declined%2C%20and%20I%20got%20good%20at%20tracking%20him%20down.%20He%20frantically%20slurred%20from%20the%20hospital%20room%20landline%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20kill%20him.%26quot%3B%20The%20doctors%20called%20it%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhallucinations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehospital-induced%20delirium%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20His%20face%20was%20gaunt%2C%20with%20a%20long%20gray%20beard.%20He%20was%20heavily%20sedated%20to%20keep%20him%20from%20ripping%20off%20all%20the%20tubes.%20I%20sat%20in%20the%20chair%20sobbing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22beeb625b-4ef2-4397-99d8-732846f84d3b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHis%20health%20declined%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20another%20doctor%20found%20my%20brother%20online.%20My%20dad%20couldn't%20communicate%20and%20was%20breathing%20with%20a%20ventilator.%20She%20urged%20us%20to%20say%20goodbye%20and%20sign%20the%20DNR.%20My%20mom%20and%20stepdad%20picked%20us%20up%2C%20and%20we%20all%20walked%20into%20the%20ICU%20in%20white%20paper%20gowns%20and%20masks.%20One%20big%20modern%20family.%20He%20looked%20like%20a%20feeble%20stranger.%20One%20eye%20was%20stuck%20open.%20It%20was%20evident%20that%20life%20was%20not%20kind%20to%20him.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20the%20first%20to%20lean%20over%20and%20talk%20to%20him.%20I%20told%20him%20I%20loved%20him%20and%20it%20was%20OK%20to%20go.%20His%20blood%20pressure%20spiked%2C%20and%20a%20single%20tear%20fell%20from%20his%20eye.%20It%20undid%20me.%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20already%20emotionally%20disconnected%20enough%20over%20the%20last%2020%20years%2C%20and%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20as%20painful.%20It%20was%20excruciating.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEveryone%20thought%20he%20would%20die%20that%20night.%20He%20didn't.%20I%20fidgeted%20at%20the%20security%20desk%20for%20my%20picture.%20Do%20you%20smile%20when%20you%20are%20visiting%20your%20dying%20father%3F%20I%20went%20every%20day%20and%20played%20Bob%20Marley's%20Three%20Little%20Birds%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BEvery%20little%20thing%20is%20gonna%20be%20all%20right.%26quot%3B%20He%20spent%20the%20last%20decade%20in%20shitty%20nursing%20homes%20accruing%20bed%20sores%20from%20neglect.%20He%20burned%20bridges%20with%20everyone%2C%20made%20unfortunate%20choices%2C%20and%20was%20catfished%20by%20someone%20in%20China%2C%20sending%20them%20whatever%20money%20he%20had.%20I%20searched%20his%20face%20for%20evidence%20of%20the%20good%20parts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22117d9bc4-3022-4e24-a608-7c7ce654c723%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20fell%20apart%20when%20he%20died%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDays%20were%20consumed%20with%20the%20heaviness%20of%20impending%20death.%20I%20cold-called%20cremation%20facilities%20from%20the%20carline%20and%20ogled%20urns%20at%20my%20kids'%20dance%20lessons.%20The%20one%20day%20I%20needed%20a%20break%20from%20visiting%20was%20when%20the%20call%20came.%20I%20fell%20apart%2C%20and%20if%20my%20husband%20hadn't%20been%20there%2C%20I%20probably%20would%20have%20hit%20the%20ground%20and%20shattered.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20opened%20the%20cardboard%20box%20that%20could%20easily%20double%20as%20an%20Amazon%20package%20for%20our%20impromptu%20funeral%20at%20my%20grandparent's%20graves.%20White%20ashes%20scattered%20from%20a%20plastic%20bag%20with%20an%20industrial-strength%20twisty%20tie.%20I%20did%20my%20part%20as%20a%20loving%20daughter%2C%20despite%20years%20of%20heartache%2C%20to%20end%20it%20with%20dignity%20and%