attention%20span%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20like%20boredom%2C%20Khader%20said%20majoring%20in%20AI%20may%20not%20be%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKhader%20said%20when%20he%20was%20getting%20his%20undergrad%20degree%2C%20he%20worked%20on%20an%20AI%20research%20project%20that%20entailed%20trying%20to%20develop%20a%20genetic%20algorithm%20that%20could%20save%20lives%20in%20a%20disaster-struck%20third-world%20country.%20Khader%20said%20the%20project%20sounded%20cool%20at%20first%2C%20but%20most%20of%20the%20four%20months%20were%20spent%20developing%20the%20simulation%2C%20which%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20AI.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20the%20last%20month%20that%20he%20dealt%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mathworks.com%2Fdiscovery%2Fgenetic-algorithm.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenetic%20algorithms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20kind%20of%20like%20irking%20me%20through%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Khader%20said.%20%26quot%3BLike%20I%20kept%20asking%20my%20research%20mentor%20like%2C%20when%20do%20we%20get%20to%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20he%20started%20working%20on%20the%20algorithm%2C%20he%20had%20to%20hyper%20tune%20it%20by%20tweaking%20certain%20variables%20to%20improve%20it.%20A%20large%20part%20of%20the%20simulation%20part%20and%20afterward%20was%20making%20slight%20enhancements%20and%20improvements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20flair%2C%20flashy%20things%20is%20very%20small%2C%26quot%3B%20Khader%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a3e73659-d318-465f-8aca-06e3e3d19e8c%5C%22%3E2.%20Math%20isn't%20your%20thing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20that%20AI%20isn't%20just%20about%20coding.%20Khader%20said%20many%20courses%20labeled%20as%20computer%20science%20were%20actually%20focused%20on%20math.%20Khader%20said%20in%20his%20TikTok%20video%20that%20his%20first%20assignment%20in%20an%20undergrad%20machine%20learning%20course%20had%20zero%20code%20and%20was%20%26quot%3Bsix%20pages%20of%20pure%20math.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20deceptive%20in%20that%20regard%2C%26quot%3B%20Khader%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20the%20formal%20number%20might%20be%20five%20or%20six%20but%20the%20actual%20number%20might%20be%20closer%20to%2015.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20AI%20math%20courses%20he%20had%20to%20take%20was%20%26quot%3Bautomata%20complexity%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20as%20he%20describes%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20letters%20and%20barely%20any%20numbers%26quot%3B%20mixed%20in%20with%20graphs%20and%20charts.%20Even%20if%20you%20are%20good%20at%20analytical%20math%20or%20problem-solving%2C%20Khader%20said%20it%20takes%20to%20get%20used%20to%20this%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheoretical%20math%2C%20I%20feel%20like%2C%20is%20a%20different%20beast%20in%20a%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20Khader%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20aren't%20familiar%20with%20it%20until%20you%20get%20to%20college.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3e2b3ea-31d9-4b3d-904e-0a8e8f292947%5C%22%3E3.%20You%20struggle%20with%20commitment%20issues%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20all%20about%20playing%20the%20long%20game%2C%20according%20to%20Khader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20video%2C%20he%20said%20that%20to%20become%20successful%20at%20a%20top%20tech%20company%2C%20you%20may%20have%20to%20get%20more%20than%20one%20degree.%20You%20also%20have%20to%20be%20committed%20to%20the%20long-term%20vision%20of%20the%20project%20because%20it%20can%20take%20time%20to%20get%20the%20results%20you%20want%2C%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20be%20the%20case%20in%20many%20evolving%20tech%20sectors.%20Meta's%20CTO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-life-not-glamorous-like-movies-meta-cto-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Bosworth%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20on%20Lenny's%20Podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%20that%20when%20he%20worked%20as%20an%20engineer%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20Facebook%2C%20he%20had%20to%20wake%20up%20every%20four%20hours%20to%20check%20an%20anti-spam%20device%20that%20he%20was%20developing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKhader%20said%20you%20also%20have%20to%20commit%20to%20the%20mindset%20of%20being%20in%20a%20constant%20state%20of%20not%20knowing%20what's%20next%20and%20still%20being%20willing%20to%20learn%20until%20you%20get%20the%20right%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20that%20commitment%2C%26quot%3B%20Khader%20said.%20%26quot%3BPhysically%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20work%20you're%20doing%2C%20but%20also%20mentally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d3075680-b772-477e-bdec-88fe3f4b9b14%5C%22%3ERemember%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20study%20AI%20to%20work%20in%20tech%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20he%20hadn't%20chosen%20computer%20science%20as%20his%20major%2C%20Khader%20said%20he%20would%20have%20chosen%20industrial%20engineering%20with%20a%20minor%20in%20computer%20science%20or%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20degree%20gives%20you%20an%20excellent%20opportunity%20to%20get%20into%20tech%2C%20while%20also%20learning%20logistical%20operations%20of%20a%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20AI%20is%20the%20hottest%20field%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%20right%20now%2C%20there%20is%20still%20a%20need%20for%20tech%20jobs%20that%20don't%20apply%20directly%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllen%20Tran%20graduated%20from%20San%20Jose%20State%20University%20with%20a%20degree%20in%20computer%20science%20in%202023.%20While%20he%20took%20an%20AI%20elective%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20stick%20with%20web%20application%20development%20over%20AI%20because%20he%20enjoyed%20seeing%20tangible%20progress%20in%20his%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20works%20at%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20he%20said%20he%20doesn't%20feel%20concerned%20about%20job%20security%20just%20because%20he's%20not%20in%20a%20role%20that%20focuses%20on%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20very%20AI-centric%20companies%2C%20they%20still%20need%20someone%20to%20build%20a%20website.%20They%20still%20need%20someone%20to%20build%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20Tran%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20still%20need%20someone%20to%20support%20services%20and%20metrics%20and%20other%20things%20that%20are%20not%20related%20to%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20may%20eventually%20want%20to%20work%20in%20AI%2C%20you%20don't%20necessarily%20need%20to%20pick%20it%20as%20a%20major.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarper%20Carroll%20is%20a%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20received%20her%20Master's%20at%20Stanford%20in%20computer%20science%20in%202022%20and%20specialized%20in%20AI.%20She%20said%20getting%20a%20degree%20in%20AI%20gives%20you%20a%20solid%20foundation%20that%20may%20help%20you%20be%20more%20effective%20at%20your%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20coding%20bootcamps%20and%20online%20courses%20available%20now%20if%20you%20want%20to%20learn%20the%20skills%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20as%20AI%20becomes%20more%20ubiquitous%20it%20makes%20sense%20that%20for%20many%20roles%2C%26quot%3B%20Carroll%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20boot%20camp%20or%20similar%20experience%20should%20suffice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20studying%20AI%20in%20college%3F%20We%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20you.%20Email%20the%20author%20at%20aaltchek%40insider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-studied-ai-on-who-should-rethink-major-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716720182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664f893f20abc1efe8fd0f22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-studied-ai-on-who-should-rethink-major-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sajjaad%20Khader%20says%20you%20might%20want%20to%20rethink%20majoring%20in%20AI%20if%20you%20fall%20into%20one%20of%20these%20three%20categories.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-studied-ai-on-who-should-rethink-major-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wreckage%20Of%20US%20Navy%20World%20War%20II%20Submarine%20Found%20After%2080%20Years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%2080%20years%2C%20the%20famed%20World%20War%20II%20U.S.%20Navy%20submarine%20USS%20Harder's%20wreck%20was%20discovered%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea.%20Located%20off%20the%20northern%20Philippine%20island%20of%20Luzon%20at%203%2C000%20feet%20(about%20900%20meters)%2C%20the%20submarine%20rests%20mostly%20intact%20except%20for%20damage%20from%20a%20Japanese%20depth%20charge%20behind%20its%20conning%20tower.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELost%20in%20battle%20on%20August%2024%2C%201944%2C%20during%20its%20sixth%20wartime%20patrol%2C%20USS%20Harder%20went%20down%20with%20its%20entire%20crew%20of%2079%20sailors%20while%20aiding%20the%20U.S.%20effort%20to%20liberate%20the%20Philippines%20from%20Japanese%20occupation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHarder%20was%20lost%20in%20the%20course%20of%20victory.%20We%20must%20not%20forget%20that%20victory%20has%20a%20price%2C%20as%20does%20freedom%2C%26quot%3B%20NHHC%20Director%20Samuel%20J.%20Cox%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20Navy%20admiral%2C%20said%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.navy.mil%2Fnews-and-events%2Fnews%2F2024%2FWWII-submarine-wreck-confirmed.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20its%20success%20in%20sinking%20two%20Japanese%20escort%20ships%20near%20Bataan%20on%20August%2022nd%2C%201944%2C%20the%20USS%20Harder%20continued%20north%20along%20the%20Luzon%20coast%20with%20two%20other%20submarines%2C%20hunting%20for%20further%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETragedy%20struck%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20August%2024th.%20Harder's%20three%20torpedoes%20missed%20their%20mark%20in%20a%20confrontation%20with%20the%20Japanese%20escort%20ship%20CD-22.%20According%20to%20captured%20Japanese%20records%2C%20the%20CD-22%20then%20relentlessly%20pursued%20Harder%2C%20ultimately%20sinking%20the%20American%20submarine%20with%20a%20depth%20charge%20attack%20on%20the%20fifth%20attempt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20wreck%20of%20the%20USS%20Harder%20was%20confirmed%20thanks%20to%20data%20provided%20by%20the%20Lost%2052%20Project.%20This%20initiative%2C%20led%20by%20Tim%20Taylor%20of%20Tiburon%20Subsea%2C%20aims%20to%20locate%20all%2052%20US%20submarines%20lost%20during%20World%20War%20II.%20Notably%2C%20the%20project%20has%20already%20successfully%20found%20at%20least%20six%20other%20submarines%20from%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20grateful%20that%20Lost%2052%20has%20given%20us%20the%20opportunity%20to%20once%20again%20honour%20the%20valour%20of%20the%20crew%20of%20the%20'Hit%20'em%20Harder'%20submarine%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20NHHC's%20Cox%20said%2C%20about%20the%20vessel's%20motto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NHHC%20said%20the%20wreck%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20final%20resting%20place%20of%20Sailors%20that%20gave%20their%20life%20in%20defence%20of%20the%20nation%20and%20should%20be%20respected%20by%20all%20parties%20as%20a%20war%20grave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Philippines%2C%20a%20US%20territory%2C%20fell%20victim%20to%20a%20surprise%20Japanese%20attack%20shortly%20after%20Pearl%20Harbor%20in%20December%201941.%20By%20spring%201942%2C%20overwhelmed%20US%20and%20Filipino%20forces%20on%20Luzon%20surrendered%2C%20allowing%20Japan%20to%20utilize%20the%20captured%20archipelago%20as%20a%20shield%20for%20its%20supply%20lines%20from%20Southeast%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20by%20mid-1944%2C%20the%20tide%20of%20the%20war%20had%20turned.%20The%20U.S.%2C%20steadily%20pushing%20back%20Japanese%20advances%20across%20the%20Pacific%2C%20planned%20to%20liberate%20the%20Philippines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnter%20the%20USS%20Harder%2C%20a%20submarine%20known%20for%20its%20aggressive%20motto%20%26quot%3BHit%20'em%20Harder.%26quot%3B%20Commanded%20by%20the%20courageous%20Captain%20Samuel%20Dealey%2C%20the%20Harder%20achieved%20remarkable%20success%20during%20its%20fifth%20patrol%20(March-July%201944).%20According%20to%20the%20National%20Medal%20of%20Honor%20Museum%2C%20the%20submarine%20sank%20three%20Japanese%20destroyers%20and%20potentially%20destroyed%20or%20heavily%20damaged%20two%20more%20within%20a%20mere%20four%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20museum%20recounts%20a%20particularly%20daring%20manoeuvre%20by%20Captain%20Dealey.%20Facing%20a%20charging%20Japanese%20destroyer%2C%20he%20ordered%20a%20daring%20%26quot%3Bdown%20the%20throat%26quot%3B%20torpedo%20attack%2C%20firing%20directly%20at%20the%20enemy's%20bow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%201%2C500%20yards%2C%20Dealey%20fired%20three%20torpedoes%20and%20ordered%20the%20sub%20to%20dive.%20%C2%A0As%20the%20Harder%20passed%2080%20feet%20underneath%20the%20destroyer%2C%20two%20of%20the%20torpedoes%20struck%20the%20ship%2C%20sending%20shock%20waves%20through%20the%20submarine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20initial%20four%20patrols%20launched%20in%20December%201942%2C%20the%20Harder%20inflicted%20significant%20damage%20on%20Japanese%20forces%2C%20sinking%2014%20warships%20and%20merchant%20vessels.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716720180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F3fmvbhr_wreckage-of-us-navy-world-war-ii-submarine_625x300_26_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fwreckage-of-us-navy-world-war-ii-submarine-found-after-80-years-5749606%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22USS%20Harder%20went%20down%20with%20its%20entire%20crew%20of%2079%20sai