ttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-manhattan-not-testify-criminal-hush-money-trial-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20turned%20his%20legal%20woes%20into%20a%20conservative%20cause%20celebre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20greatest%20test%20of%20that%20strategy%20could%20arrive%20as%20soon%20as%20next%20week.%20Closing%20arguments%20in%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-hush-money-trial-case-evidence-michael-cohen-payment-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EManhattan%20hush%20money%20criminal%20trial%20%3C%2Fa%3Eare%20expected%20to%20occur%20on%20Tuesday.%20Twelve%20New%20Yorkers%20will%20then%20weigh%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20historic%20verdict%3A%20finding%20the%20first-ever%20former%20president%20guilty%20in%20a%20criminal%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolling%20shows%20that%20a%20guilty%20verdict%20has%20some%20potential%20peril.%20But%20the%20strongest%20possibility%20is%20that%20voters%20will%20tune%20it%20out%20entirely%20in%20favor%20of%20economic%20issues%2C%20on%20which%20Trump%20scores%20far%20higher%20than%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d74a966f-447d-4f5d-8eab-e533b81690c0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EVoters%20are%20paying%20attention%20to%20the%20trial%20but%20have%20thus%20far%20largely%20discounted%20it.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20his%20allies%20might%20not%20have%20to%20spin%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20Quinnipiac%20University%20nationwide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpoll.qu.edu%2Fpoll-release%3Freleaseid%3D3896%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoll%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2062%25%20of%20voters%20said%20a%20guilty%20verdict%20would%20not%20affect%20their%20vote%20in%20November.%20In%20comparison%2C%20just%2021%25%20said%20it%20would%20change%20their%20minds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Cook%20Political%20Report%20polling%20partnership%20that%20surveyed%20seven%20battleground%20states%20found%20that%2040%25%20of%20voters%20said%20Trump's%20legal%20woes%20had%20no%20impact%20on%20their%20support%20or%20were%20unsure.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20same%20survey%20found%20voters%20were%20broadly%20aware%20of%20Trump's%20problems%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20hush%20money%20trial%2C%20a%20previous%20civil%20fraud%20trial%2C%20and%20a%20separate%20civil%20trial%20that%20found%20the%20former%20president%20liable%20for%20sexually%20assaulting%20columnist%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-e-jean-carroll-defamation-damages-sexual-abuse-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20E.%20Jean%20Carroll%3C%2Fa%3E%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVoters%20were%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cookpolitical.com%2Fsurvey-research%2F2024-swing-state-project%2Funique-election-driven-traditional-issue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easked%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Cook%20partnership%20whether%20they%20were%20more%20concerned%20about%20Biden's%20age%20or%20Trump's%20temperament%20and%20legal%20issues.%20Narrowly%20(53%25%20to%2047%25)%2C%20they%20said%20Biden's%20age%20was%20more%20concerning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f99877d-2390-40da-b47c-638167ad4fd7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20has%20rallied%20Republicans%2C%20but%20the%20broader%20public%20isn't%20entirely%20convinced.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20repeatedly%20shown%20he%20can%20rally%20Republicans%20to%20his%20side%20when%20his%20legal%20problems%20mount.%20But%20the%20average%20voter%20is%20not%20a%20GOP%20member%20of%20Congress%20nor%20responding%20to%20Trump's%20fundraising%20appeals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20Trump's%20and%20allies'%20efforts%20to%20cast%20doubt%20on%20the%20entire%20prosecution%2C%20some%20polls%20have%20found%20that%20Americans%20see%20legitimacy%20in%20the%20process.%20A%20Yahoo%20News%2FYouGov%20poll%20found%20that%20since%20last%20month%2C%20the%20hush%20money%20trial's%20approval%20has%20increased%20slightly%3B%20there's%20now%20a%2012-point%20margin%20of%20approval%20(49%25-37%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20many%20voters%20are%20sympathetic%20to%20some%20of%20Trump's%20claims.%20A%20recent%20New%20York%20Times%2FSiena%20College%20poll%20of%20voters%20in%20key%20battleground%20states%20found%20that%20among%20registered%20voters%2C%20slightly%20more%20(49%25)%20thought%20that%20the%20former%20president%20would%20not%20get%20a%20fair%20trial%20than%20those%20who%20did%20(45%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20there%20is%20one%20clear%20takeaway%20from%20recent%20polling%20it's%20that%20the%20American%20people%20do%20think%20the%20former%20president%20did%20something%20wrong%2C%20even%20if%20he%20may%20not%20have%20broken%20the%20law.%20The%20same%20Yahoo%20poll%20found%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20Americans%20(52%25)%20believe%20Trump%20falsified%20business%20records%20%26quot%3B%20to%20conceal%20a%20hush%20money%20payment%20to%20a%20porn%20star%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20charge%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20Manhattan%20case.%20The%20Quinnipiac%20survey%20that%20showed%20voters%20may%20not%20be%20motivated%20by%20the%20trial%20also%20found%20that%2046%25%20of%20voters%20believe%20Trump%20did%20something%20illegal%20%E2%80%94%20another%2027%25%20believe%20he%20did%20something%20unethical%20but%20not%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20responses%20are%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-republicans-gop-trial-vp-candidate-vice-president-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20GOP%20officials%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20led%20by%20Speaker%20Mike%20Johnson%2C%20who%20have%20slammed%20the%20trial%20as%20a%20sham.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump%20listens%20during%20his%20Manhattan%20criminal%20trial.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650d512a961b37edf39d727%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221684%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20Manhattan%20criminal%20trial%20is%20set%20to%20consider%20closing%20arguments%20on%20Tuesday.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Lane-Pool%2FGetty%20Images)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286a69879-d030-4194-a144-231d8e7cc460%5C%22%3ETrump's%20reaction%20will%20loom%20over%20the%20verdict.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20never%20been%20one%20to%20take%20setbacks%20lightly.%20He's%20under%20a%20gag%20order%20that%20does%20not%20allow%20him%20to%20criticize%20witnesses%2C%20the%20jury%2C%20or%20Merchan's%20daughter.%20Once%20the%20verdict%20is%20in%2C%20Trump%20can%20unleash%20whatever%20criticism%20he%20desires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20hard%20to%20imagine%20that%20in%20responding%20to%20a%20potential%20guilty%20verdict%20Trump%20lashes%20out%20in%20a%20way%20that%20causes%20him%20more%20problems.%20His%20attacks%20on%20judges%20have%20historically%20triggered%20some%20of%20the%20rare%20instances%20when%20Republicans%20speak%20out%20more%20broadly%20against%20him.%20It%20was%20then-Speaker%20Paul%20Ryan%20who%20called%20Trump's%20suggestion%20that%20a%20federal%20judge%20couldn't%20fairly%20adjudicate%20a%20case%20because%20of%20his%20Mexican%20heritage%20the%20%26quot%3Btextbook%20definition%26quot%3B%20of%20racism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20has%20constantly%20been%20able%20to%20count%20on%20almost%20all%20of%20his%20fellow%20Republicans.%20The%20FBI's%20decision%20to%20search%20Mar-a-Lago%20marked%20another%20point%20of%20vulnerability%20for%20Trump.%20Almost%20immediately%2C%20top%20GOP%20officials%20rallied%20to%20his%20side.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen-House%20Minority%20Leader%20Kevin%20McCarthy%20proclaimed%20that%20the%20Justice%20Department%20had%20reached%20an%20%26quot%3Bintolerable%20state%20of%20weaponized%20politicization.%26quot%3B%20Even%20former%20Vice%20President%20Mike%20Pence%2C%20who%20had%20been%20harshly%20critical%20of%20Trump%2C%20expressed%20concern%20abou